SIMPLE: prognosticate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prognosticate
<hw>Prog*nos"ti*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Prognosticated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prognosticating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Prognostic</er>.]</ety> <def>To indicate as future; to foretell from
signs or symptoms; to prophesy; to foreshow; to predict; <as>as, to
<ex>prognosticate</ex> evil</as>.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I neither will nor can <qex>prognosticate</qex>⟦br⟧
To the young gaping heir his father's fate.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To foreshow; foretoken; betoken; forebode;
presage; predict; prophesy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prognostication</ent>⟦br⟧
